          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Current of the bunched triton beam was held below 4 nA."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Water target was solid (ice) in a thin-walled stainless",
                "steel cup with one face in direct contact with the",
                "accelerator vacuum. Cooling the target from the",
                "outside by direct contact with liquid nitrogen in a",
                "small cryostat of styrofoam maintained the solid phase",
                "of the water."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 2x2 in. liquid scintillator (NE213) was used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two pulse-height biases were used simultaneously",
                " (Compton edge of Cs-137 and of Na-22). The flight path",
                "was 3.53 m, the total time resolution was 2.1 ns."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Cross sections were derived from the high-energy",
                "portions of the yield curves."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "1-H-1(T,N)2-HE-3,,DA",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "1-H-1(T,N)2-HE-3,,DA",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "1-H-1(T,N)2-HE-3",
                        "target": "1-H-1",
                        "projectile": "T",
                        "process": "N",
                        "product": "2-HE-3",
                        "quantity": ",DA",
                        "data_type": null,
                        "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                        "quantity_236": ",DA"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                " By comparing the measured yield",
                "from this reaction with the calculated yield the",
                "experimental setup was calibrated. Standard gas targets",
                "were used.",
                "Energy dependence of the efficiency of the neutron",
                "detector was determined by measuring neutron yields of",
                "the reactions H-2(t,n)He-4 and H-1(t,n)He-3 at about 30",
                "energy points between 2.2 and 36.9 MeV and comparing",
                "them with well-known cross sections."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The attenuation correction due to nonelastic processed",
                "is quite small and introduces negligible errors.",
                "However, multiple scattering in the target and its",
                "structure which was not corrected for is estimated to",
                "affect the data by as much as 4%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "   Errors given in a table are from counting",
                "statistics only.",
                "Common scale error is composed of 3.5% calibration",
                "error, the current integrator calibration error (<0.5%)",
                "and the systematic portion of the attenuation error",
                " (<0.5%), adding up to about 4%.",
                "Uncertainty of the specific energy loss of the tritons",
                "in water contributes to the common scale error.",
                "Uncertainty of the zero-degree position was +-0.2",
                "degree.",
                "Uncertainties in the integrated charge and in the dead",
                "time were each < 0.5%."
              ]
            }
          ],
